  "texts": [
    "• GEN-SCL This method distinguishes between input aspects, such as implicit and explicit aspects and opinions.",
    "• GEN-NAT This method adapts to a new structured generation format that can better capture the quadruple information in Table 10.",
    "Based on the mapping of the four elements (c, a, o, s) to their corresponding semantic values (x c, x a, x o, x s), the generation format for GEN-NAT is as follows::",
    "The GEN-SCL-NAT model achieved promising results on the ACOS-Dataset, especially on sentences with implicit sentiment expressions, as shown in Table 8.",
    "However, when dealing with longer and more complex examples, output structure validity issues may arise for the GEN-SCL-NAT and PARAPHRASE (Zhang et al. 2021a) models."
